The paper discusses reinforcement learning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community (cs.LG). The use of deep learning techniques is also mentioned, which further supports the likelihood of cs.LG. The paper also discusses the challenges of learning in partially observable environments, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed algorithm is designed for domains that involve decision-making, which is a common theme in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm using various challenging hierarchical POMDPs, which is a topic that falls under the category of mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
